Description: This project implements a basic calculator in C that performs fundamental arithmetic operations: addition, subtraction, multiplication, and division. The calculator operates via a command-line interface.
Code Structure
SimpleCalculator/
│
├── src/
│   ├── calculator.c
│   ├── calculator.h
│   └── main.c
│
├── tests/
│   └── test_calculator.c
│
├── Makefile
├── README.md
└── LICENSE
Functionality and Analysis
calculator.c
Purpose: Implements core arithmetic operations.

Functions:

double add(double a, double b)

Description: Adds two numbers.
Parameters:
a (double): First number
b (double): Second number
Returns: The sum of a and b.
double subtract(double a, double b)

Description: Subtracts the second number from the first.
Parameters:
a (double): Number to subtract from
b (double): Number to be subtracted
Returns: The result of a - b.
double multiply(double a, double b)

Description: Multiplies two numbers.
Parameters:
a (double): First number
b (double): Second number
Returns: The product of a and b.
double divide(double a, double b)

Description: Divides the first number by the second. Handles division by zero.
Parameters:
a (double): Numerator
b (double): Denominator
Returns: The result of a / b. Returns 0.0 if b is zero.
